This paper is focused on natural language understanding and common-sense reasoning, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses machine learning (cs.LG) and complexity theory (cs.CC) in the context of evaluating common-sense reasoning models. Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of security and privacy (cs.CR) in the context of preventing unjustified conclusions.
